      "content": "While that specific batch didn't show the crashes, pushing the build as-is is precisely the risky move the board is there to prevent. That particular memory spike suggests a dangerous edge case in high-load scenarios, and trusting sporadic log silence against a known architecture flaw is not a viable engineering strategy. I cannot recommend a launch that knowingly sweeps a critical, unstably spotted bug under the rug in exchange for retail window momentum. I recommend we postpone the full launch to Wednesday for a definitive patch to ensure customer trust and avoid the much larger reputational hit of a failed Day 1 experience.",
